HEADWORD: Mucedin
<hw>Mu*ce"din</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Mucus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot. Chem.)</fld> <def>A yellowish white,
amorphous, nitrogenous substance found in wheat, rye, etc., and
resembling gluten; -- formerly called also
<altname>mucin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
